channel.title: Live: World Championship Artistic Gymnastics
channel.desc: The apparatus finals get underway on the penultimate day of the World Gymnastics Championships in Jakarta with great medal chances for Great Britain on the men's floor. Harry Hepworth, Luke Whitehouse and Jake Jarman have some of the most difficult routines in the World. And after winning World Cup gold last month in the Vault, Abi Martin could challenge for a medal on her World Championship debut. Champions will also be crowned in the men's pommel Horse, the rings and the women's uneven bars.
